{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8756eef5-5627-4e53-965f-56446d9aabec","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` **natively** uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform for MTP-enabled projects. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a .NET 9 bridge and is **no longer needed**. You can simply remove it:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01TwxWVmfrzKJTH678urHc5V","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01W2FA5DS6dwzJCp8JGLVdRJ","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-f00307b2ad7048f7874a1bd06944fa40/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":"\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-f00307b2ad7048f7874a1bd06944fa40/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"d67df360-67dc-4dd4-86ef-787c9d3fa856","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about MTP support. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. That property was needed in .NET 9 and earlier to opt into the MTP-based test runner via `dotnet test`.\n\nIn .NET 10:\n- `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively when the test project is an MTP project (e.g., has `EnableMSTestRunner`).\n- The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed and can be removed.\n\n\nNow I'll help clean up their project file to remove that obsolete property.","outputTokens":450,"requestId":"A02B:3C520:C669A8:E7BC24:69FE877A"},"id":"2d75b295-91dc-4f47-9343-484354b232e9","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:01:55.178Z","parentId":"c1117a08-c1ef-45f9-b166-d2d6ef9de645"}
