{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5e0e8bab-928c-4682-b14d-14e56253e181","content":"Here's the summary:\n\n**What changed:** Removed `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>`.\n\n**Why:** In .NET 9, that property was required to make `dotnet test` route through Microsoft.Testing.Platform instead of the legacy VSTest adapter. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` **natively detects** MTP projects (like yours, which sets `EnableMSTestRunner`) and uses the MTP runner automatically. The property is now a no-op.\n\n**Your remaining setup is sufficient:**\n- `EnableMSTestRunner` → builds your test project as an MTP executable\n- `OutputType: Exe` → required for MTP runner mode\n- `MSTest 3.8.0` → provides the MTP integration\n\nJust run `dotnet test` as usual — it will use MTP under the hood.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d67df360-67dc-4dd4-86ef-787c9d3fa856","outputTokens":211,"requestId":"A028:17D0EF:C96B47:EAD0B3:69FE8788"},"id":"0d698449-b485-4ad1-8f0a-e7cd06507e8e","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:02:06.169Z","parentId":"5606e0ea-8e9b-45e4-a31f-fef1c77df457"}
